requirements_rfc2119:
  description: "Verify AIMP requirement documents use RFC 2119 keywords on every numbered requirement."
  match:
    include:
      - "docs/requirements/*.md"
  review:
    strategy: individual
    instructions: |
      Review this requirements document for formal requirement discipline.

      Check that:
      1. Every numbered requirement item uses at least one RFC 2119 keyword
         (MUST, MUST NOT, SHALL, SHALL NOT, SHOULD, SHOULD NOT, MAY, REQUIRED,
         RECOMMENDED, OPTIONAL).
      2. Requirement section headings follow `### AIMP-NNN.M: Title`, where
         `AIMP-NNN` matches the filename prefix and `.M` numbering is
         sequential without gaps.
      3. The file begins with `# AIMP-NNN: Title` and includes an `## Overview`
         section before the `## Requirements` section.
      4. Each numbered item states one verifiable claim; vague or untestable
         language is flagged.
      5. Existing requirement IDs are not renumbered or reassigned.

      Output Format:
      - PASS: The requirements document follows the AIMP format and RFC 2119 discipline.
      - FAIL: Issues found. List each issue with a line reference and concise description.

pinned_test_amendment:
  description: "Require an AIMP-001 amendment in the same change when pinned requirement tests are modified."
  match:
    include:
      - "test/**/*.test.ts"
      - "docs/requirements/AIMP-*.md"
  review:
    strategy: all_changed_files
    additional_context:
      unchanged_matching_files: true
    instructions: |
      Review the changed files for pinned-test governance.

      Tests carrying the two-line traceability comment
      `THIS TEST VALIDATES A HARD REQUIREMENT (AIMP-NNN.M)` /
      `YOU MUST NOT MODIFY THIS TEST UNLESS THE REQUIREMENT CHANGES.`
      are pinned to docs/requirements/AIMP-001-core-loop.md.

      Check that:
      1. Any modification or deletion of a pinned test is accompanied by a
         corresponding amendment to the referenced AIMP-001 requirement in the
         same change. Amend the requirement document FIRST; the test change
         must match the amended requirement text.
      2. New tests may be pinned to existing requirements without an
         amendment; adding a traceability comment to an unchanged test also
         needs no amendment.
      3. A changed requirement whose pinned tests still assert the old
         behavior is flagged as stale coverage.
      4. Traceability comments reference real requirement IDs that exist in
         docs/requirements/.

      Output Format:
      - PASS: Pinned tests and AIMP-001 amendments are consistent in this change.
      - FAIL: List each pinned test changed without a corresponding AIMP-001 amendment (or stale requirement/test pair) with file and line references.
